<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Day Two</h4>



<p>Day 2 is for the lower body and upper body. Walking lunges challenge the legs, particularly the quads, and glutes, while incline dumbbell bench presses target the upper chest and shoulders.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Pull-ups and barbell deadlifts contribute to a powerful back and overall upper body strength. The decline barbell bench press further engages the chest, and the barbell bent over rows enhances back development. This balanced approach promotes growth and improved strength in both upper and lower body muscle groups.</p>



